.Dd @MDOCDATE@
.Dt RINGMASTER 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm ringmaster
.Nd llama-server control-plane daemon
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Cm daemon
.Op Fl -socket Ar path
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
is a long-lived per-user daemon that spawns and supervises
.Xr llama-server 1
processes on behalf of clients such as
.Xr circus 1
and
.Xr clown 1 .
Each
.Xr llama-server 1
child is identified by an alias and listed in an in-memory registry;
ringmaster reaps the child when it exits, with or without a
.Cm StopInstance
request.
.Pp
Clients talk to
.Nm
over a Unix domain socket using newline-delimited JSON-RPC 2.0.
See
.Xr ringmaster 7
for the architecture and
.Xr clown-plugin-protocol 7
for unrelated background on the clown plugin protocol.
.Pp
.Nm
is intended to run under
.Xr launchd 8
on macOS and
.Xr systemd.user 5
on Linux; the
.Sx programs.ringmaster
home-manager module configures the appropriate service unit on each
platform.
Single-instance only: one
.Nm
daemon per user manages every
.Xr llama-server 1
child.
.Sh SUBCOMMANDS
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Cm daemon Op Fl -socket Ar path
Run the control-plane daemon.
Listens on the path resolved from
.Fl -socket
when present, the
.Ev RINGMASTER_SOCKET
environment variable when set, or
.Pa $HOME/.local/state/circus/control.sock
otherwise.
Accepts connections until SIGTERM/SIGINT, at which point in-flight
RPCs drain and the listener closes.
.El
.Sh ENVIRONMENT
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Ev RINGMASTER_SOCKET
Override the control socket path.
Both
.Nm
itself and its clients
.Pq Xr circus 1 , Xr clown 1
read this variable, so setting it consistently in the user's
environment is sufficient.
.It Ev XDG_LOG_HOME
Resolves the canonical log directory.
.Nm
itself does not write a log file; the home-manager service units
route stderr to systemd journal (Linux) or to
.Pa $XDG_LOG_HOME/ringmaster.log
.Pq Pa ~/.local/log/ringmaster.log
when the variable is unset (macOS).
.El
.Sh FILES
.Bl -tag -width "~/.local/state/circus/control.sock"
.It Pa ~/.local/state/circus/control.sock
Default control socket path.
.It Pa ~/.local/log/ringmaster.log
Default log file on macOS when
.Ev XDG_LOG_HOME
is unset.
.It Pa ~/.local/share/circus/models
Directory scanned for downloadable GGUF files by the
.Cm ListAvailableModels
RPC.
.El
.Sh RPC SURFACE
.Nm
implements seven JSON-RPC 2.0 methods:
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Cm StartInstance Ar alias Ar model Op Ar bind Op Ar args
Spawn a new
.Xr llama-server 1
child with the given
.Fl -alias .
The
.Fl -model
argument resolves to
.Pa ~/.local/share/circus/models/<model>.gguf
when not absolute.
.Fl -bind
defaults to
.Sq 127.0.0.1 ;
.Fl -args
is passed through to llama-server.
The call blocks until
.Pa /health
returns 200 (60-second timeout).
.It Cm StopInstance Ar alias
Send SIGTERM to the child's process group, wait up to five seconds,
then SIGKILL if it didn't exit.
Removes the entry from the registry.
.It Cm StopAll
Best-effort: snapshot the registry, call
.Cm StopInstance
for each alias.
Returns the list of aliases that were stopped.
.It Cm ListInstances
Return every alias known to the registry along with its bind/port/PID
and start time.
.It Cm GetInstance Ar alias
Same shape as
.Cm ListInstances
but for a single alias.
Returns
.Sy -32001
when the alias is not registered.
.It Cm ListAvailableModels
Scan the on-disk models directory and return each
.Pa *.gguf
file's name, absolute path, and size.
.It Cm DownloadModel Ar name
Fetch a model from the embedded registry, verify its SHA-256, and
move it atomically into the models directory.
Synchronous (no progress events on the wire) — use
.Xr circus 1
.Cm download
for the bubbletea progress UI.
.El
.Sh SIGNALS
.Bl -tag -width SIGINT
.It Dv SIGTERM
Drain in-flight RPCs and exit cleanly.
Children are NOT killed; they continue running and will be re-adopted
by the next
.Nm
process if it restarts before they exit.
.It Dv SIGINT
Same as
.Dv SIGTERM .
.El
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr circus 1 ,
.Xr clown 1 ,
.Xr llama-server 1 ,
.Xr ringmaster 7 ,
.Xr ringmaster-testing 7
.Sh CAVEATS
.Nm
single-Wait contract: only one goroutine inside the daemon ever calls
.Xr exec.Cmd.Wait 3
for each child.
Both the
.Cm StopInstance
path and the unexpected-exit reaper read the same
.Sq exited
channel rather than reaping independently.
If you embed
.Nm Ap s
launcher in your own code, preserve this invariant.
.Sh AUTHORS
.An "amarbel, LLC"
